<taxonomicName authority="Baird, 1858" authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1858" box="[858,1282,559,592]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hispidus">Perognathus hispidus Baird, 1858</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation box="[697,1244,603,632]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">Charco Escondido, Tamaulipas, Mexico.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[696,1292,559,986]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
Based on detailed sequencing of nDNA and mtDNA genes, C. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1858" box="[1039,1144,677,710]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hispidus">hispidus</taxonomicName>
is one of the three “ancient” clades of coarse-haired pocket mice. Three subspecies are recognized, following the 2012 revision by J. J. Andersen and J. E. Light.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
